Source: [[Patterns of enterprise applications architecture]]

Scalability can be horizontal (when you just add more hardware/servers), or vertical (when you upgrade your current server/code). Often it's more desirable to build the system to be horizontally scalable, because adding new hardware is usually cheaper than adding more people.
